Halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the onion to the pan and stir-fry until starting to soften, ~{6-7%minutes}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Halve the @tenderstem broccoli{80%g}(halved lengthways). Trim the @green beans{150%g}(trimmed and chopped into thirds).

Once the onions are starting to soften, add the @sliced mushrooms{120%g} to the pan along with a drizzle of @oil{}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, sandwich each @british chicken breast{2} between two pieces of #baking paper{} or #cling film{}. Pop onto a #board{}, then give it a bash with a #rolling pin{} or the bottom of a #saucepan{} until it's 1-2cm thick.

Put the @plain flour{1.5%tbsp} in a #bowl{} with the @indonesian style spice mix{1%sachet} and a good pinch of @salt{} and some @pepper{}. Mix together.

Lay your chicken breast in the bowl of seasoned flour, then toss to ensure the chicken gets an even coating. Repeat for the remaining chicken.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Once the mushrooms have browned, add the Tenderstem® and green beans to the pan. Stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then reduce the heat to medium. Add the @ginger puree{15%g} and garlic, stir fry for ~{1%minute} more.

Add a splash of @water{}, then cover with a #lid{} (or #foil{}) and allow to cook until tender, ~{4-6%minutes} more. Remove from the heat.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in another large frying pan on medium-high heat.

Once hot, lay in the chicken. Fry until golden brown and cooked through, ~{5-6%minutes} on each side.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Transfer the chicken to a board, cover with foil and rest for a couple of minutes.

While the chicken is resting, pop the pan of veg back on medium-high heat.

Add the @hoisin sauce{96%g}, @water{50%ml}(for the sauce) and @udon noodles{220%g} to the pan. Toss to coat and simmer until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove from the heat. Taste and add @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed. Add a splash of @water{} to loosen if you feel it needs it.

Share your ultimate yaki style udon between your #bowls{}. Thinly slice the chicken and serve on top. Drizzle the @honey{30%g} over the chicken and sprinkle over the @roasted white sesame seeds{5%g} to finish.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop in a bowl of hot water for 1 minute.

Enjoy!